The paper discusses the effectiveness and limitations of Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) for representation learning of graphs. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.LG. Additionally, the paper presents a theoretical framework for analyzing the expressive power of GNNs, which could also fall under cs.AI. The paper also discusses the empirical validation of their theoretical findings on graph classification benchmarks, which could fall under cs.CL, cs.CV, or cs.NE depending on the specific benchmarks used.
